headline: New York Post to Expand Into California With L.A.-Based Publication
summary: The New York Post is trying its luck in La La Land.  The  News Corp  -owned tabloid plans to launch a West Coast version called The California Post and based in Los Angeles early next year, The New York Post Media Group said Monday.  The California Post, which will be based in Los Angeles, will focus on sports, entertainment and local and business news from the region and have a digital website and mobile app, in addition to a print edition.
